PHP Arrays and Superglobals
Array is ordered map associating a value in array with a key.
	This is because arrays in PHP use hash tables.
	Key default is 0 based index but can be either string or integer.
	Create new array:
		$arrayName = array();
		can also initialize with:
			$arrayName = array["one", "two"]; or
			$arrayName = ["one", "two"];
	Append to array:
		$arrayname[] = "item"; appends to end
		$arrayname[i] = "item"; pretty obvious...
	Create array with key and value
		$arrayName = array(0 => "zero", 1 => "one");
		$arrayName = array("zero" => 0, "one" => 1);

	Print item:
		echo $arrayName[key];

Creating new object of class is same as C.
$object = new Class();
$object->property = "";
ex.	$person->firstName = "name";
Constructors
	define __construct() as function (two underscores)
this-> refers to object

Class Person
	function __construct($firstname, $lastname){
		$this->firstname = $firstname;
		$this->lastname = $lastname;
	}
}